cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with image processing and specifically with image inpainting and impulse noise removal. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of sparse and low rank decomposition, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of ADMM method for solving the decomposition problem suggests the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves numerical optimization, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Mathematical Software). Finally, the paper involves the use of local image statistics, which suggests the category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
